==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|la|acanthus}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἄκανθος}}, from {{m|grc|ἀκή||thorn}} + {{m|grc|ἄνθος||flower}}.<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976}}</ref><ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5}}</ref>

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/əˈkæn.θəs/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/əˈkæn.θəs/}}
* {{rhymes|en|ænθəs}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es|acanthi}}

# A member of the genus ''[[Acanthus]]'' of [[herbaceous]] [[prickly]] plants with toothed leaves, (family [[Acanthaceae]], order {{taxlink|Scrophulariales|order|noshow=1}}) found in the south of Europe, Asia Minor, and India.{{defdate|First attested in the mid 16th century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|architecture}} An ornament resembling the [[foliage]] or leaves of {{taxlink|Acanthus spinosus|species|noshow=1}}, used in the [[capital]]s of the [[Corinthian]] and [[composite]] orders.{{defdate|First attested in the mid 18th century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

